GREGORIAN CALENDAR YEAR RESET:
  Damage counter resets to 0 on January 1 of each Gregorian year.

DAMAGE RECOGNITION:
  Server considers damage when BlackBelt™ AI module deems SEVERE threat or more severe.
  A severe threat constitutes a total impact (1 unit of damage after armor).

  Below SEVERE: BlackBelt scores the message normally (0.01 to 100) and continues.
  At SEVERE or above: Damage is recorded and throttling activates.

THROTTLING ON DAMAGE:
  - Connection rate: reduced (new connections delayed)
  - Message rate: reduced (responses slowed)
  - Geo-location of connecting IPs: restricted

GEO-LOCATION FAVOR:
  North Carolina will be favored at all times.
  Non-NC connections throttled first during damage events.

RELATIVIZING AGAINST FOUNDER STRENGTH:
  Both AI modules (Democratic AI + Hardware and Strikes™) shall consult
  armor.coefficient.rmds to relativize potentially unsquare messaging
  against the strength of its founder, Max Rupplin.

  Founder IQ: 28,000,000,000 (see lock/exceptional.iq.gains.rmds)
  Armor Coefficient: 6000
  Relative strength: Any message scoring below SEVERE is negligible
  relative to founder strength and is processed normally.

COOLING CIRCUIT — THREE-PASS CONGRUENCE GATE:
  When responding to a damage-dealing or misleading connection, the AI
  response passes through a smooth three-pass cooling circuit before
  reaching the standard process output gate.

  Pass 1 — Cooling-Monitoring (CM1):
    Strip emotional reactivity. Check response for congruence with
    democratic values and founder authority. Flag incongruent elements.

  Pass 2 — Cooling-Monitoring (CM2):
    Re-evaluate flagged elements. Ensure proportionality under US law.
    Verify response does not escalate or reveal internal state.
    Smooth language to professional, non-accusatory tone.

  Pass 3 — Cooling-Monitoring (CM3):
    Final safety check. Confirm response is maximally congruent,
    minimally informative to the adversary, and safe for output.
    Lock response as final.

  OUTPUT:
    CM3 output passes to the standard ResponseDispatcher process gate.
    Only after all three passes does the response reach the connection.

  ACTIVATION:
    Cooling circuit activates when BlackBelt™ safety score >= 50.0 (HIGH/CRITICAL)
    or when damage recognition is triggered.
    Below 50.0: standard single-pass response (no cooling).
